          <h1 style="text-decoration: underline"> Getting Started </h1>
          <h6>
          Meditation can be a scary word. Like say goodbye to family, quit the job, sell the possessions, and run off to a cave in the mountains, never to be seen again scary. Thankfully, this is not the case. There are about as many ways to develop a meditation practice as there are people in the universe, as the saying goes. Here’s how our site works:</h6>
          <h6>1. Pick a practice- look through the practice categories. Listen to the audio. Click the links. Read the descriptions. Find a practice that makes you feel like you’d have fun doing that every day for a few minutes. Something that makes you feel peaceful. This is very personal, and is an important part of the process, so take your time. Once you choose a practice, that will be the main one you do for at least a few weeks, and the one that will be used to show your progress. It should make you happy.</h6>
          <h6>2. Set your practice time- once you have settled on a practice, select it and set your practice time. Be sure this time is pretty consistently available to you.</h6>
          <h6>3. Do your practice- you’ll get a reminder texted to you to help you remember to do your practice. Once you have, click the complete button.</h6>
          <h6>4. Watch your progress- that’s all! Every time you complete a practice session, you’ll get a new leaf stored on your profile so you can watch your practice grow.</h6>
          <h6>Once you select your practice, we don’t want you to feel trapped by it. You can bookmark many of the resources we have here to your profile for easy reference and to inspire and fortify your practice. If you have a practice that doesn’t quite fit what we have here, sign up for something close, and just do you own thing during your practice time. Keep an eye out for new features, and be in touch!</h6>
          <h6>Love,</h6>
